The pilot reported that during landing, the airplane encountered a wind gust, landed hard and 
bounced several times. The nose gear collapsed and the airplane skidded to a stop, which 
resulted in substantial damage to the engine firewall. 
The pilot reported no preimpact mechanical malfunctions or failures with the airplane that 
would have precluded normal operation.
The pilot's inadequate flare and failure to maintain aircraft control during landing in gusty 
wind conditions.
